<h2>
  <a name="7-we-need-a-modal-%E2%86%92-raw-ltdialoggt-endraw-" href="#7-we-need-a-modal-%E2%86%92-raw-ltdialoggt-endraw-">
  </a>
  7. “We need a modal” → <code>&lt;dialog&gt;</code>
</h2>

<p>It’s honestly nice that browsers finally stepped up and said: fine, here’s your modal 😄 No more installing 12KB libraries just to open a dialog that users love so much. This one is also accessible by default, so win-win.<br>
</p>

<div class="highlight js-code-highlight">
<pre class="highlight html"><code><span class="nt">&lt;dialog</span> <span class="na">id=</span><span class="s">"modal"</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>
  <span class="nt">&lt;p&gt;</span>Are you sure you want to deploy on Friday?<span class="nt">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
  <span class="nt">&lt;button</span> <span class="na">onclick=</span><span class="s">"modal.close()"</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>Cancel<span class="nt">&lt;/button&gt;</span>
  <span class="nt">&lt;button</span> <span class="na">onclick=</span><span class="s">"alert('Good luck 😬')"</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>Deploy<span class="nt">&lt;/button&gt;</span>
<span class="nt">&lt;/dialog&gt;</span>

<span class="nt">&lt;button</span> <span class="na">onclick=</span><span class="s">"modal.showModal()"</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>Open modal<span class="nt">&lt;/button&gt;</span>
</code></pre>
