<h2>
  <a name="but-dont-get-me-wrong" href="#but-dont-get-me-wrong">
  </a>
  ⚠️ But don’t get me wrong
</h2>

<p>Libraries are great. Sometimes you absolutely need them. But sometimes… you’re installing a dependency for something the browser solved years ago. Before installing anything, just ask yourself (or Google): “Is the browser already smarter than me here?” Sometimes the answer is yes. And that’s… perfectly fine 😄</p>


