          ">
          <p>The <code>&lt;dialog&gt;</code> one hits hard. I recently audited a site where the modal library alone added 14KB gzipped to the bundle — for something the browser does natively with better accessibility out of the box.</p>

<p>The <code>loading="lazy"</code> point is especially relevant for anyone running image-heavy pages at scale. I manage a site with thousands of pages across 12 languages and switching from a JS lazy-loading library to native <code>loading="lazy"</code> shaved ~200ms off LCP on mobile. That's the kind of win that directly impacts Core Web Vitals scores.</p>

<p>Would love to see a follow-up on native CSS features that replace JS too — <code>scroll-snap</code>, <code>container queries</code>, and <code>@layer</code> have quietly eliminated a lot of JS-heavy patterns.</p>


