          <p>I like <code>requestIdleCallback</code>. I read about a pattern you can implement with it: idle-until-urgent:<br>
There are some expensive calculations required for some function the user is likely to invoke. Instead of doing it once it is required, you can do it once you have time for it. Basically pre-caching.<br>
But: when the result is required before the work was done, you cancel the callback and do it just-in-time.</p>


